---
import DocumentationLayout from '../layouts/DocumentationLayout.astro';
import Callout from '../components/sections/Callout.astro';
import { buildWebPageJsonLD } from '../utils/seo';

const jsonLD = buildWebPageJsonLD({
  title: 'Get Started with aDNA',
  description: 'Set up your first aDNA project in three steps: clone the template, open in your editor, and run your first agent session with Claude Code.',
  url: Astro.url.href,
});
---

<DocumentationLayout
  title="Get Started"
  description="Set up your first aDNA project in three steps: clone the template, open in your editor, and run your first agent session with Claude Code."
  jsonLD={jsonLD}
>
  <p>Get your first aDNA project running in about 5 minutes.</p>

  <Callout variant="info" title="Prerequisites">
    <p>Git, and <a href="https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/claude-code" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Claude Code</a> installed via <code>npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code</code>.</p>
  </Callout>

  <Callout variant="tip" title="What you'll have when you're done">
    <p>A working aDNA project with <code>CLAUDE.md</code> + the <code>what/</code> / <code>how/</code> / <code>who/</code> triad. Run <code>claude</code> inside the folder and your agent reads the governance files automatically.</p>
  </Callout>

  <h2 id="step-1">1. Clone the template</h2>
  <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/LatticeProtocol/Agentic-DNA.git my-project
cd my-project</code></pre>

  <h2 id="step-2">2. Open in your editor</h2>
  <p>Open in Obsidian, VS Code, or any Markdown editor. <code>CLAUDE.md</code> at the root is your agent's entry point.</p>

  <h2 id="step-3">3. Run your first session</h2>
  <p>Start Claude Code. It reads <code>CLAUDE.md</code>, detects a fresh project, and walks you through onboarding:</p>
  <pre><code>$ claude
✓  Loaded CLAUDE.md (project instructions)

I can see this is a fresh aDNA project. Let's set your project
identity and create your first session file.

What is this project called, and what problem does it solve?
&gt; _</code></pre>

  <h2 id="next-steps">Next steps</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/learn/tutorials/first-claude-md">Tutorial: Create Your First CLAUDE.md</a></li>
    <li><a href="/learn/what-is-adna">What is aDNA?</a></li>
    <li><a href="/learn/concepts/triad">Learn about the Triad</a></li>
    <li>See it live: the <a href="https://github.com/LatticeProtocol/aDNA-aDNA" target="_blank" rel="noopener">aDNA.aDNA repository</a> is a working aDNA project — every concept demonstrated in a real vault.</li>
  </ul>
</DocumentationLayout>
